            {
              "id": "07b54faa-df97-395a-9283-9c7ed63bc99d",
              "name": "Nonconstant string passed to execute or addBatch method on an SQL statement",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "\nThe input values included in SQL queries need to be passed in safely. Bind variables in prepared statements can be used to easily mitigate the risk of SQL injection. Alternatively to prepare statements, each parameter can be escaped manually.\n\n**Solution (Prepared Statements):**\n\n```java\nString query = \"SELECT * FROM User WHERE id = ?\";\nPreparedStatement preparedStatement = connection.prepareStatement(query);\npreparedStatement.setString(1, inputId);\nResultSet resultSet = preparedStatement.executeQuery();\n```\n\n**Solution (Encoding):**\n\n```java\nimport org.owasp.esapi.Encoder;\ncreateQuery(\"select * from User where id = '\" + Encoder.encodeForSQL(inputId) + \"'\");\n```\n\n## In Context Remediation\n```\nVulnerable Query: \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = '\" + name + \"' AND auth_tan = '\" + auth_tan + \"'\"\nRemediated Query: ## Description\n\nThis code builds an SQL query by concatenating untrusted values directly into the statement text. In Java, this allows attacker-controlled input to change the meaning of the query, bypass filters, or retrieve and modify unintended data.\n\nThe fix is to use a PreparedStatement with placeholders for every external value. Parameter binding keeps user input as data instead of executable SQL and is the standard JDBC defense against SQL injection for queries like this one.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nReplace all string-built SQL with parameterized JDBC queries. Bind every user-controlled value with the appropriate setter such as setString, setInt, or setLong, and never concatenate request parameters into SQL text.\n\nIf dynamic query structure is unavoidable, restrict selectable columns, sort directions, and table names to a fixed allowlist before composing the SQL. Apply least-privilege database accounts and centralized input validation, but do not rely on validation or escaping as a substitute for prepared statements.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\n~~~java\nString sql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = ? AND auth_tan = ?\";\n\ntry (PreparedStatement stmt = connection.prepareStatement(sql)) {\n    stmt.setString(1, name);\n    stmt.setString(2, auth_tan);\n\n    try (ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery()) {\n        // process results\n    }\n}\n~~~\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\n~~~java\nimport java.sql.PreparedStatement;\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\n~~~\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP SQL Injection](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/SQL_Injection)\n- [OWASP SQL Injection Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/SQL_Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html)\n- [Java PreparedStatement API](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/sql/PreparedStatement.html)\n\n```\n#### Remediation 1\nBelow is a minimal **Java console** example showing the vulnerable query and the **safe** version using a **PreparedStatement**.\n\n### `pom.xml` dependencies\n```xml\n<dependencies>\n    <!-- In-memory demo database -->\n    <dependency>\n        <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n        <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n        <version>2.2.224</version>\n    </dependency>\n</dependencies>\n```\n\n### `Main.java`\n```java\nimport java.sql.*;\n\npublic class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n        String url = \"jdbc:h2:mem:test;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\";\n\n        try (Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection(url, \"sa\", \"\")) {\n            setup(con);\n\n            String name = \"Smith\";\n            String authTan = \"' OR '1'='1\"; // injection payload\n\n            System.out.println(\"Vulnerable count: \" + vulnerable(con, name, authTan));\n            System.out.println(\"Safe count: \" + safe(con, name, authTan));\n        }\n    }\n\n    static void setup(Connection con) throws SQLException {\n        try (Statement st = con.createStatement()) {\n            st.execute(\"CREATE TABLE employees (id INT PRIMARY KEY, last_name VARCHAR(50), auth_tan VARCHAR(50))\");\n            st.execute(\"INSERT INTO employees VALUES (1, 'Smith', 'abc123')\");\n            st.execute(\"INSERT INTO employees VALUES (2, 'Jones', 'xyz789')\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Similar to:\n    // SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = '\" + name + \"' AND auth_tan = '\" + auth_tan + \"'\n    static int vulnerable(Connection con, String name, String authTan) throws SQLException {\n        String sql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = '\" + name +\n                     \"' AND auth_tan = '\" + authTan + \"'\";\n        try (Statement st = con.createStatement();\n             ResultSet rs = st.executeQuery(sql)) {\n            return count(rs);\n        }\n    }\n\n    static int safe(Connection con, String name, String authTan) throws SQLException {\n        String sql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = ? AND auth_tan = ?\";\n        try (PreparedStatement ps = con.prepareStatement(sql)) {\n            ps.setString(1, name);\n            ps.setString(2, authTan);\n            try (ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery()) {\n                return count(rs);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    static int count(ResultSet rs) throws SQLException {\n        int n = 0;\n        while (rs.next()) n++;\n        return n;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Expected result\n- **Vulnerable count** may return rows because injected input changes query logic.\n- **Safe count** returns `0` unless values exactly match stored data.\n\n### Alternative JDBC drivers\n- PostgreSQL:\n```xml\n<dependency>\n    <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>\n    <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>\n    <version>42.7.3</version>\n</dependency>\n```\n- MySQL:\n```xml\n<dependency>\n    <groupId>com.mysql</groupId>\n    <artifactId>mysql-connector-j</artifactId>\n    <version>8.4.0</version>\n</dependency>\n```\n- SQLite:\n```xml\n<dependency>\n    <groupId>org.xerial</groupId>\n    <artifactId>sqlite-jdbc</artifactId>\n    <version>3.46.0.0</version>\n</dependency>\n```\n\n#### Remediation 2\n```xml\n<!-- pom.xml -->\n<dependencies>\n  <!-- In-memory DB for easy repro -->\n  <dependency>\n    <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    <version>2.2.224</version>\n  </dependency>\n</dependencies>\n```\n\n```java\n// Main.java\nimport java.sql.*;\n\npublic class Main {\n  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    String url = \"jdbc:h2:mem:test;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\";\n\n    try (Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection(url);\n         Statement st = con.createStatement()) {\n\n      st.execute(\"CREATE TABLE employees (\" +\n          \"userid INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR(50), last_name VARCHAR(50), auth_tan VARCHAR(50))\");\n      st.execute(\"INSERT INTO employees VALUES \" +\n          \"(1,'Alice','Smith','ABC123'),\" +\n          \"(2,'Bob','Jones','XYZ789')\");\n\n      String name = \"Smith\";\n      String authTan = \"x' OR '1'='1\"; // injection attempt\n\n      // Vulnerable:\n      String sql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = '\" + name +\n          \"' AND auth_tan = '\" + authTan + \"'\";\n      try (ResultSet rs = st.executeQuery(sql)) {\n        int count = 0;\n        while (rs.next()) count++;\n        System.out.println(\"Vulnerable rows returned: \" + count);\n      }\n\n      // Safe:\n      String safeSql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = ? AND auth_tan = ?\";\n      try (PreparedStatement ps = con.prepareStatement(safeSql)) {\n        ps.setString(1, name);\n        ps.setString(2, authTan);\n        try (ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery()) {\n          int count = 0;\n          while (rs.next()) count++;\n          System.out.println(\"PreparedStatement rows returned: \" + count);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nExpected output:\n```text\nVulnerable rows returned: 1\nPreparedStatement rows returned: 0\n```\n\nWhy this prevents SQL injection:\n- `PreparedStatement` sends SQL structure separately from user data.\n- `name` and `authTan` are treated as values, not executable SQL.\n\nRelevant fix for the original query:\n```java\nString sql = \"SELECT * FROM employees WHERE last_name = ? AND auth_tan = ?\";\nPreparedStatement ps = connection.prepareStatement(sql);\nps.setString(1, name);\nps.setString(2, auth_tan);\n```\n\nAlternative JDBC drivers/databases:\n- PostgreSQL: `org.postgresql:postgresql`\n- MySQL: `com.mysql:mysql-connector-j`\n- MariaDB: `org.mariadb.jdbc:mariadb-java-client`\n- SQLite: `org.xerial:sqlite-jdbc`\n\n___\n\n\n**References (SQL injection)**\n\n- [CAPEC-66: SQL Injection](https://capec.mitre.org/data/definitions/66.html)\n- [CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html)\n- [OWASP: Top 10 A03_2021-Injection](https://owasp.org/Top10/A03_2021-Injection/)\n- [OWASP: SQL Injection Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://www.owasp.org/index.php/SQL_Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet)\n- [OWASP: Query Parameterization Cheat Sheet](https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Query_Parameterization_Cheat_Sheet)\n\n\n"
