              "id": "1b953f26-5c39-330d-a08b-19121a81b942",
              "name": "File Disclosure",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Disclosure Vulnerability in Spring File\" is a type of vulnerability in Java programming language that occurs when an attacker is able to manipulate the `setViewName` method in Spring MVC to access restricted files. This can lead to unauthorized access to sensitive data or even code execution.\n\nThe specific vulnerability sink in the provided code is:\n\n```java\nmodelAndView.setViewName(VIEW_FORMATTER.formatted(\"success\"));\n```\n\nIn this case, the `setViewName` method is being used to set the view name for the `ModelAndView` object. If an attacker can manipulate the input to the `formatted` method, they could potentially access restricted files.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it's recommended to:\n\n- Always validate and sanitize user inputs. Never trust user inputs blindly.\n- Use a whitelist of allowed view names and reject any input that does not match the whitelist.\n- Avoid exposing internal file paths to the user.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nA possible fix for the provided code could be:\n\n```java\nString viewName = VIEW_FORMATTER.formatted(\"success\");\nif (isAllowedViewName(viewName)) {\n    modelAndView.setViewName(viewName);\n} else {\n    throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid view name: \" + viewName);\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, the `isAllowedViewName` method checks if the view name is in a whitelist of allowed view names.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Spring MVC\n- Java SE (Standard Edition)\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017: A1-Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [CWE-22: Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/22.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are valid and active for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
