              "id": "2f767934-6605-3856-96ea-12bc63254442",
              "name": "Spring Endpoint",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe Spring Endpoint Vulnerability is a type of security vulnerability that occurs when an application exposes sensitive information or functionality through its endpoints. This can happen when the application does not properly validate or restrict access to these endpoints. In the context of Spring Framework, endpoints are routes or URLs where the application's functionality can be accessed.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the vulnerability lies in the `userRepository.save(newUser);` line. If the `newUser` object is populated with user-supplied data, an attacker could potentially manipulate this data to perform malicious actions, such as SQL Injection, Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), or even Remote Code Execution (RCE).\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should:\n\n1. Always validate user-supplied data: Ensure that the data is in the expected format and does not contain any malicious input.\n\n2. Implement proper access control: Only authenticated and authorized users should be able to access sensitive functionality.\n\n3. Use parameterized queries or prepared statements: This can help prevent SQL Injection attacks.\n\n4. Encode data that will be output to the user: This can help prevent XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a simple fix for the provided code snippet:\n\n```java\ntry {\n  // Validate newUser object\n  if (isValid(newUser)) {\n    userRepository.save(newUser);\n    return newUser;\n  } else {\n    throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid user data\");\n  }\n} catch (Exception ex) {\n  log.error(\"Error creating new User\", ex);\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\nIn this fix, the `isValid()` function should contain the necessary validation logic for the `newUser` object.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet seems to be using Spring Data JPA, so the following dependencies are required:\n\n- Spring Boot Starter Data JPA\n- Spring Boot Starter Web\n- A database connector, such as MySQL Connector Java or PostgreSQL JDBC Driver\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A1 Injection](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A1_2017-Injection)\n- [OWASP Top 10 - A5 Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A5_2017-Broken_Access_Control)\n- [CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-89",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "3.0",
