            {
              "id": "3bc78992-7881-309e-b91a-3943a261dc8e",
              "name": "User Controlled Data Can Lead To XSS Vulnerabilities",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nCross-Site Scripting (XSS) is a type of security vulnerability that enables attackers to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. In the context of jQuery's `.append(...)` function, this vulnerability can occur when user-controlled data is directly passed into the function. This is considered an anti-pattern in secure coding practices.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, `$(\"#votesList\").append(voteTemplate);`, the `voteTemplate` variable is appended as HTML to the `votesList` element. If an attacker can control the content of `voteTemplate`, they could potentially inject malicious scripts, leading to an XSS attack.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this risk, you should always treat user-controlled data as untrusted. Avoid directly injecting user-controlled data into the DOM. Instead, use text node creation or safe methods to handle user-controlled data.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of using `.append()`, you can use `.text()` if you want to add text content. This method ensures that the passed content is treated as text and not interpreted as HTML.\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#votesList\").text(voteTemplate);\n```\n\nIf you need to add HTML content, make sure to sanitize the user-controlled data before appending it. You can use a library like DOMPurify to sanitize HTML.\n\n```javascript\nvar sanitizedTemplate = DOMPurify.sanitize(voteTemplate);\n$(\"#votesList\").append(sanitizedTemplate);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following libraries:\n\n- jQuery\n- DOMPurify (for the sanitized version)\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
