            {
              "id": "45e508d7-08c3-30e3-b281-b473a0889f1c",
              "name": "Exposes User Listing Without Authorization Checks",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Unrestricted User Listing Exposure due to Lack of Authorization Checks\" is a security vulnerability that occurs when an application does not properly implement authorization checks, allowing unauthorized users to access sensitive information. In this case, the vulnerability allows unauthorized users to retrieve a list of all users from the database.\n\nThis vulnerability is a type of Broken Access Control vulnerability, which is a common and serious security issue. It can lead to unauthorized information disclosure, modification or destruction of all user data, and even full takeover of the system.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should:\n\n1. Implement proper authorization checks before accessing sensitive data. Only authorized users should be able to access sensitive information.\n2. Use the principle of least privilege. Users should only have the permissions necessary to perform their tasks.\n3. Regularly review and update your access control policies and procedures.\n4. Use secure coding practices to prevent security vulnerabilities.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a simple way to fix the vulnerability in the provided code:\n\n```java\n// Get the authenticated user\nAuthentication auth = SecurityContextHolder.getContext().getAuthentication();\nUser currentUser = userRepository.findByUsername(auth.getName());\n\n// Check if the user has the necessary permissions\nif (currentUser.hasRole(\"ADMIN\")) {\n    List<User> allUsers = userRepository.findAllUsers();\n} else {\n    throw new AccessDeniedException(\"You do not have permission to perform this action.\");\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, we first get the authenticated user. Then, we check if the user has the necessary permissions to access the list of all users. If the user does not have the necessary permissions, we throw an `AccessDeniedException`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Spring Security\n- Spring Data JPA\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A5_2017-Broken_Access_Control)\n- [Access Control Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Access_Control_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-285: Improper Authorization](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/285.html)"
              },
