              "id": "6c45eec8-768f-3d01-927a-c6cea5393144",
              "name": "User Controlled Data In HTML String May Result In XSS",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet above is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. XSS is a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. The vulnerability occurs when an application includes untrusted data in a new web page without proper validation or escaping, or updates an existing web page with user-supplied data using a browser API that can create HTML or JavaScript.\n\nIn this case, the vulnerability arises from the concatenation of user-controlled data (`user`) directly into the URL string used in the AJAX request. An attacker could manipulate the `user` variable to include malicious scripts, which would then be executed when the AJAX request is made.\n\n## Mitigation\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should:\n\n1. **Validate Input**: Ensure that the user-controlled data is what you expect. For example, if `user` is supposed to be a username, ensure it only contains alphanumeric characters.\n\n2. **Encode Output**: Ensure that user-controlled data is properly encoded so it's safe to display. For example, use JavaScript's `encodeURIComponent()` function to encode the `user` variable before including it in the URL.\n\n3. **Use Appropriate Response Headers**: To prevent XSS in HTTP responses that aren't intended to contain any HTML or JavaScript, you can use the `Content-Type` and `X-Content-Type-Options` headers to ensure that browsers interpret the responses the way you intend.\n\n## Code Fix\n\nHere's how you could modify the code to mitigate the vulnerability:\n\n```javascript\n$.ajax({\n    url: 'JWT/votings/login?user=' + encodeURIComponent(user),\n    contentType: \"application/json\"\n}).always(function () {\n    getVotings();\n})\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
