              "id": "717229af-8663-336e-8812-6f2ab211729e",
              "name": "Insecure Access Control Based On Resource Identifier",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nInconsistent Identifier Access Grant Vulnerability, also known as Insecure Direct Object References (IDOR), occurs when an application provides direct access to objects based on user-supplied input. As a result, attackers can bypass authorization and directly access resources in the system.\n\nIn the provided code, the application is vulnerable to IDOR because it does not perform any access control checks before returning the requested user profile. An attacker could potentially manipulate the `userId` parameter to access other users' profiles.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, the application should implement proper access control checks to ensure that the authenticated user has the necessary permissions to access the requested resource. This can be achieved by comparing the authenticated user's ID with the ID of the user profile being requested.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```java\nif (userId != null && userId.equals(authUserId)) {\n    UserProfile requestedProfile = new UserProfile(userId);\n    if (requestedProfile.getUserId() != null\n        && requestedProfile.getUserId().equals(authUserId)) {\n      return success(this)\n          .feedback(\"idor.view.profile.success\")\n          .output(requestedProfile.profileToMap().toString())\n          .build();\n    } else {\n      return failed(this).feedback(\"idor.view.profile.close1\").build();\n    }\n} else {\n    return failed(this).feedback(\"idor.view.profile.close2\").build();\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code does not explicitly import any libraries, so it's not possible to list any library dependencies without additional context.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017: A5-Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A5_2017-Broken_Access_Control)\n- [CWE-639: Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/639.html)"
              },
