            {
              "id": "7310a782-517c-34bd-9986-885f5f88d266",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability In jQuery HTML Manipulation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Dynamic Input Vulnerability in jQuery HTML Manipulation: Sanitization and Plain Text Content\" is a common security vulnerability in JavaScript programming language. It occurs when an application does not properly sanitize user input before using it in HTML manipulation functions, such as jQuery's `.html()` method. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the application is using the `.html()` method to insert the value of `votes[i]` into an HTML element with the id `nrOfVotes` + `i`. If the `votes[i]` value is not properly sanitized and contains malicious scripts, it can lead to XSS attacks.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always sanitize user input before using it in HTML manipulation functions. You can use jQuery's `.text()` method instead of `.html()`, as it automatically escapes HTML tags and prevents XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the fixed version of the provided code snippet:\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#nrOfVotes\" + i).text(votes[i]);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [DOM Based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
