              "id": "805df9c0-c31e-3ebe-8ee3-dd00116d1d16",
              "name": "Missing Validation For Required Security Keys",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Insufficient Validation of Optional Security Keys Vulnerability\" in Java refers to a situation where the application does not validate or improperly validates the optional security keys. This can lead to unauthorized access or manipulation of data. In the provided code, the security questions are not properly validated. If an attacker submits a request without the security questions or with incorrect security questions, the application will still process the request.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to validate all the security keys properly. The application should reject any request that does not contain the required security keys or contains incorrect security keys. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is the recommended fix for the provided code:\n\n```java\npublic boolean verifyAccount(Integer userId, HashMap<String, String> submittedQuestions) {\n    // short circuit if no questions are submitted or if the submitted questions do not match the stored questions\n    if (submittedQuestions.entrySet().size() != secQuestionStore.get(verifyUserId).size() || \n        !submittedQuestions.keySet().equals(secQuestionStore.get(verifyUserId).keySet())) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    for (String key : submittedQuestions.keySet()) {\n        if (!submittedQuestions.get(key).equals(secQuestionStore.get(verifyUserId).get(key))) {\n            return false;\n        }\n    }\n\n    // else\n    return true;\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code does not seem to require any specific library dependencies to execute properly.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP - Input Validation Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Input_Validation_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-345: Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/345.html)"
