            {
              "id": "92c743e2-2f43-36a5-91bc-9d15b18e7f0f",
              "name": "Unsafe String Injection Into XML",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nPotential XML Injection Vulnerability is a type of security vulnerability that occurs when an application assembles XML statements from user-controlled data. This can allow an attacker to control the structure of the XML, which can lead to unauthorized data access, data corruption, denial of service, and other serious consequences.\n\nIn the provided Java code, the vulnerability exists because the application is directly appending user-controlled data (`field1`) to an XML statement without properly sanitizing or encoding it.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to:\n\n1. Avoid constructing XML documents using string concatenation.\n2. Use a safe API that provides a parameterized interface, or has built-in XML encoding.\n3. If a safe API is not available, sanitize and encode user-controlled data before including it in an XML document.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nA safer way to construct the XML document in the provided code would be to use a library like `javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder` to create and append elements:\n\n```java\nimport javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory;\nimport javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Document;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Element;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Text;\n\nDocumentBuilderFactory dbf = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();\nDocumentBuilder db = dbf.newDocumentBuilder();\nDocument doc = db.newDocument();\n\nElement p = doc.createElement(\"p\");\nText text = doc.createTextNode(\"We have charged credit card:\" + field1);\np.appendChild(text);\n\ncart.append(p);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- `javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder`\n- `javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory`\n- `org.w3c.dom.Document`\n- `org.w3c.dom.Element`\n- `org.w3c.dom.Text`\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [CWE-611: Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference ('XXE')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/611.html)"
              },
