            {
              "id": "95be1d29-6ee4-3384-b92d-bdc778160a0e",
              "name": "Endpoint Exposes Internal Promo Codes",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Exposure of Server-Side Coupon and Promo Codes\" vulnerability refers to a situation where an application inadvertently exposes sensitive information, such as coupon or promo codes, to unauthorized users. In the provided Java code, the server-side coupon code is exposed to the client-side, which could potentially be exploited by malicious users.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to:\n\n- Avoid exposing sensitive information, such as coupon or promo codes, to the client-side.\n- Implement proper access control mechanisms to ensure that only authorized users can access sensitive information.\n- Use secure communication protocols, such as HTTPS, to protect sensitive information during transmission.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nThe following code snippet demonstrates how to fix the vulnerability:\n\n```java\n@GetMapping(value = \"/coupons/{code}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\npublic ResponseEntity<CheckoutCode> getDiscountCode(@PathVariable String code, Principal principal) {\n  if (principal == null || !checkoutCodes.isAuthorized(principal.getName(), code)) {\n    return new ResponseEntity<>(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n  }\n  return ResponseEntity.ok(checkoutCodes.get(code).orElse(new CheckoutCode(\"no\", 0)));\n}\n\n@GetMapping(value = \"/coupons\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\npublic ResponseEntity<CheckoutCodes> all(Principal principal) {\n  if (principal == null || !checkoutCodes.isAuthorized(principal.getName())) {\n    return new ResponseEntity<>(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n  }\n  List<CheckoutCode> all = Lists.newArrayList();\n  all.addAll(this.checkoutCodes.getCodes());\n  return ResponseEntity.ok(new CheckoutCodes(all));\n}\n```\n\nIn this revised code, we have added a `Principal` parameter to the methods, which represents the currently authenticated user. We then check if the user is authorized to access the requested coupon code or all coupon codes. If the user is not authorized, we return a 403 Forbidden status code.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- Spring Web\n- Google Guava\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP Top Ten: A2-Broken Authentication](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A2_2017-Broken_Authentication)\n- [CWE-200: Information Exposure](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/200.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-200",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/200.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-200"
                ]
              }
