            {
              "id": "9a914a35-d91d-398d-8cea-9eb508e9c673",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability In jQuery HTML Manipulation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nDynamic Input Vulnerability in jQuery HTML Manipulation: Sanitization and Plain Text Content is a type of vulnerability that occurs when an application does not properly sanitize user input before appending it to the DOM. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. In the provided code example, the user's comment is directly appended to the `#list` element without any sanitization, which can lead to XSS if the comment contains malicious scripts.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to sanitize user input before appending it to the DOM. This can be done by using the `text()` method instead of `append()`, which ensures that the input is treated as plain text and not interpreted as HTML. Alternatively, you can use a library or a function that specifically sanitizes HTML input to ensure that any potentially harmful scripts are removed.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the provided code:\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#list\").append($('<li>').text(comment));\n```\n\nIn this version, the `text()` method is used to ensure that the comment is treated as plain text and not interpreted as HTML.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
