              "id": "a4df066f-8bff-3e25-ad00-39a1720363d2",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability With Dynamic innerHTML",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nCross-Site Scripting (XSS) is a type of security vulnerability that enables attackers to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. A web application is vulnerable to XSS if it uses unsanitized user input. XSS attacks occur when an attacker uses a web application to send malicious code, generally in the form of a browser side script, to a different end user.\n\nIn JavaScript, the `innerHTML` property can be used to get or replace the content of HTML elements. However, if the content is added dynamically and includes user input, it can lead to an XSS vulnerability. This is because an attacker can include a script in the user input that will be executed when the HTML is rendered by the browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate XSS vulnerabilities due to dynamic input in `innerHTML`, you should always sanitize user input. This means that you should encode or escape special characters so that they are not interpreted as code by the browser. \n\nIn addition, you should use text content instead of HTML when possible, as this will prevent any HTML tags from being interpreted as code. If you need to include dynamic HTML, consider using safer methods like `textContent` or `innerText`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of:\n\n```javascript\nnewdiv.innerHTML = html;\n```\n\nYou should use:\n\n```javascript\nnewdiv.textContent = html;\n```\n\nOr, if you need to include HTML:\n\n```javascript\nnewdiv.innerHTML = sanitizeHTML(html);\n```\n\nWhere `sanitizeHTML` is a function that properly escapes special characters.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not require any library dependencies to execute properly.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
