              "id": "a5c6aa65-35f1-3892-b2b4-edd7657cf7cc",
              "name": "Unsafe String Injection Into XML",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nPotential XML Injection due to Unsafe String vulnerability in Java programming language occurs when user-supplied data is included in an XML document without proper validation or escaping, allowing an attacker to control the structure of the XML. This can lead to a variety of attacks such as disclosure of confidential data, denial of service, server side request forgery, port scanning from the perspective of the machine where the parser is located, and other system impacts.\n\nIn the provided code snippet, the `totalSale` variable is directly appended to the `cart` string without any validation or escaping. If `totalSale` contains malicious XML content, it could lead to XML Injection.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to:\n\n1. Validate user input: User input should be validated and sanitized before it is processed. This can be done using a whitelist of allowed input.\n\n2. Use XML encoding: Special characters in user input should be encoded before they are included in an XML document.\n\n3. Use a safe API: Use an API or a library that automatically handles XML encoding and ensures that user input cannot change the structure of the XML document.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nA safer way to append the `totalSale` to the `cart` string would be to use `String.format()` method:\n\n```java\ncart.append(String.format(\"                               $%.2f\", totalSale));\n```\n\nThis ensures that `totalSale` is treated as a floating point number and not as a string that could contain malicious XML content.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not require any additional library dependencies to execute properly.\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [CWE-91: XML Injection (aka Blind XPath Injection)](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/91.html)"
              },
