            {
              "id": "a89fc23f-4087-3ab1-83de-d6459fafd308",
              "name": "User Controlled Data In HTML String May Result In XSS",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code above is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. XSS is a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. In this case, the vulnerability arises from the fact that user-controlled data (`result[i].UserID`, `result[i].FirstName`, `result[i].LastName`, `result[i].SSN`, `result[i].Salary`) is directly included in an HTML string without proper sanitization or encoding. An attacker could potentially manipulate the data to include malicious scripts, which would then be executed when the HTML is rendered in a user's browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always encode user-controlled data before including it in an HTML string. This can be done using JavaScript's built-in functions for HTML encoding, or by using a trusted library that provides this functionality. Additionally, you should use context-specific encoding when inserting user-controlled data into different HTML contexts (HTML content, attribute, JavaScript, CSS, URL).\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a simple fix using JavaScript's built-in `encodeURIComponent` function to encode user-controlled data:\n\n```javascript\nfor (var i = 0; i < result.length; i++) {\n    html = html + '<tr id = \"' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].UserID) + '\"</tr>';\n    html = html + '<td>' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].UserID) + '</td>';\n    html = html + '<td>' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].FirstName) + '</td>';\n    html = html + '<td>' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].LastName) + '</td>';\n    html = html + '<td>' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].SSN) + '</td>';\n    html = html + '<td>' + encodeURIComponent(result[i].Salary) + '</td>';\n    html = html + '</tr>';\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires jQuery library to execute properly.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE-79): Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
