            {
              "id": "af11fbb7-9c0a-3b3a-9772-51ef6c70a66d",
              "name": "User Controlled Data In HTML String May Result In XSS",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nA potential Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability can occur when user-controlled data is used in an HTML string. In the provided JavaScript code, the `result` variable, which is concatenated to a base64 image string, could potentially be controlled by a user. If an attacker can control this `result` variable, they could inject malicious scripts that would be executed when the HTML string is rendered by a web browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to properly sanitize and escape user-controlled data before using it in HTML strings. This can be done by using built-in JavaScript functions or third-party libraries that are designed to prevent XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\n```javascript\nvar sanitizedResult = encodeURIComponent(result);\ndocument.getElementById(\"previewRemoveUserInput\").src = \"data:image/png;base64,\" + sanitizedResult;\n```\n\nIn the above code, the `encodeURIComponent()` function is used to sanitize the `result` variable. This function encodes special characters, which prevents them from being interpreted as part of an HTML string.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code does not require any library dependencies to execute properly.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
