              "id": "b1685b05-2426-39f2-a283-680aefea184d",
              "name": "JQuery Html Function Can Lead To XSS",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. This is due to the use of jQuery's `.html()` function, which can interpret any HTML tags included in the input string as actual HTML. If an attacker can control the `data.name`, `data.color`, or `data.size` values, they could inject malicious scripts that would be executed in the context of the user's browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid using the `.html()` function with user-controlled input. Instead, use jQuery's `.text()` function for plain strings, which will not interpret any HTML tags in the input string. If you need to include HTML tags in the output, use a function that properly escapes any potentially dangerous characters, such as `HtmlUtils.setHtml()`.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is a fixed version of the code:\n\n```javascript\nwebgoat.customjs.jquery('#idor-profile').text(\n    'name:' + data.name + '\\n'+\n    'color:' + data.color + '\\n'+\n    'size:' + data.size + '\\n'\n);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following libraries to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n- WebGoat's custom JavaScript library\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE-79): Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-79"
                ]
              }
