            {
              "id": "b6273711-a275-3533-8086-7d43200174ab",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability In jQuery HTML Manipulation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Dynamic Input Vulnerability in jQuery HTML Manipulation: Sanitization and Plain Text Content\" is a type of Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability that occurs when user-supplied data is improperly validated or escaped before being used as input to jQuery's HTML manipulation methods such as `.append()`. This can allow an attacker to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users, leading to a variety of attacks such as stealing user data, performing actions on behalf of the user, or defacing web content.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to properly sanitize and escape all user-supplied input before using it in jQuery's HTML manipulation methods. This can be done by using jQuery's `.text()` method, which automatically escapes HTML and prevents script execution, or by using a trusted library or function to sanitize the input.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of directly appending the `server` variable to the `#servers` element, you should first create a new text node with the `server` value, and then append this text node to the `#servers` element. This ensures that any HTML tags in the `server` value are automatically escaped and not executed as script.\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#servers\").append(document.createTextNode(server));\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
