            {
              "id": "c609d9d9-270f-3f34-9e75-e51149f324c3",
              "name": "Spring Endpoint",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. This is a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. XSS attacks occur when an application includes untrusted data in a new web page without proper validation or escaping, or updates an existing web page with user-supplied data using a browser API that can create HTML or JavaScript.\n\nIn this case, the application is taking user input (the comment text) and storing it without properly sanitizing it. If the user input contains malicious scripts, they will be stored and executed when the comment is displayed.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always validate and sanitize user input. This can be done using a secure coding library or framework that provides input validation and output encoding functions. \n\nYou should also set the HttpOnly flag for cookies to prevent them from being accessed by client-side scripts, and use Content Security Policy (CSP) to restrict the sources of scripts and other resources.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nYou can use the `HtmlUtils.htmlEscape()` method from the Spring Framework to sanitize the user input:\n\n```java\nimport org.springframework.web.util.HtmlUtils;\n\n// ...\n\nComment comment = parseJson(commentStr);\n\nList<Comment> comments = userComments.getOrDefault(webSession.getUserName(), new ArrayList<>());\ncomment.setDateTime(LocalDateTime.now().format(fmt));\ncomment.setUser(webSession.getUserName());\n\n// Sanitize the comment text\nString sanitizedText = HtmlUtils.htmlEscape(comment.getText());\ncomment.setText(sanitizedText);\n\ncomments.add(comment);\nuserComments.put(webSession.getUserName(), comments);\n\nif (comment.getText().contains(phoneHomeString)) {\n  return (success(this).feedback(\"xss-stored-comment-success\").build());\n} else {\n  return (failed(this).feedback(\"xss-stored-comment-failure\").build());\n}\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\n- Spring Framework\n- Java Time API\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
