              "id": "c81189de-3270-3ddd-89bd-de9f3ec2b614",
              "name": "User Controlled Data In HTML String May Result In XSS",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet above is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. XSS is a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. In this case, the vulnerability arises from the fact that user-controlled data is being directly used in HTML strings without proper sanitization or encoding. This allows an attacker to inject malicious scripts, which will be executed in the context of the victim's browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always treat user input as untrusted data. You should use context-specific output encoding/escaping techniques on all user-supplied data before including it in HTML output. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nIn the given code, the user-controlled data is being directly included in the HTML output. To fix this, you should use a method that properly escapes or encodes the user-controlled data. Here is a fixed version of the code:\n\n```javascript\n$.get(\"SqlInjectionMitigations/servers?column=\" + column, function (result, status) {\n    $(\"#servers\").empty();\n    for (var i = 0; i < result.length; i++) {\n        var server = html.replace('ID', $('<div/>').text(result[i].id).html());\n        var status = \"success\";\n        if (result[i].status === 'offline') {\n            status = \"danger\";\n        }\n        server = server.replace('ONLINE', $('<div/>').text(status).html());\n        server = server.replace('STATUS', $('<div/>').text(status).html());\n        server = server.replace('HOSTNAME', $('<div/>').text(result[i].hostname).html());\n        server = server.replace('IP', $('<div/>').text(result[i].ip).html());\n        server = server.replace('MAC', $('<div/>').text(result[i].mac).html());\n        server = server.replace('DESCRIPTION', $('<div/>').text(result[i].description).html());\n        $(\"#servers\").append(server);\n    }\n});\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library dependencies:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
