              "id": "d2032d3d-784f-3940-a46a-d04b33808f2b",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability In jQuery HTML Manipulation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Dynamic Input Vulnerability in jQuery HTML Manipulation: Sanitization and Plain Text Content\" is a type of Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability that occurs when user-supplied data is improperly validated or escaped before being used as input to jQuery's HTML manipulation methods such as `.append()`, `.html()`, etc. This can allow an attacker to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users, leading to a variety of attacks such as stealing user data, performing actions on behalf of the user, etc.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to properly validate and sanitize all user-supplied input before using it in jQuery's HTML manipulation methods. This can be done by using jQuery's `.text()` method instead of `.html()`, `.append()`, etc., as it automatically escapes any HTML tags in the input, preventing script injection.\n\nAdditionally, consider using Content Security Policy (CSP) to restrict the sources from which scripts can be loaded, further reducing the risk of XSS attacks.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the vulnerable line of code with the following:\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#votesList\").append($('<div>').text(voteTemplate));\n```\n\nThis code creates a new `<div>` element, sets its text content to `voteTemplate` (automatically escaping any HTML tags), and appends it to `#votesList`.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## OWASP and CWE Links\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
