              "id": "f8f3d588-5f46-31ef-a1f6-dba1bb208087",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability In jQuery HTML Manipulation",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"Dynamic Input HTML Manipulation in jQuery: Sanitization and Plain Text Content Vulnerability\" is a common security vulnerability in JavaScript programming language. It occurs when an application includes user-controllable data in its output that is interpreted as HTML without effectively validating or encoding it. This can lead to various attacks such as Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, it is recommended to always validate and sanitize user input before using it in your application. This can be done by using a secure method that encodes special characters from the input, such as `text()` in jQuery or `innerText` in JavaScript.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of using `append()`, which can interpret the input as HTML, use `text()` to treat the input as plain text:\n\n```javascript\n$(\"#toast\").text(result);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example requires the following library to execute properly:\n\n- jQuery\n\n## OWASP and CWE Resources\n\n- [OWASP Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)](https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/xss/)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-79"
                ]
              }
